data.value: It's Simple 1. Select the Sitecore Version you want to upgrade to. 2. Upgrade DotNet Framework. 3. Save and build solution. 4. Commit Changes. 5. Upgrade Packages. 6. Build and Fix the errors. 7. Commit changes. 8. Upgrade Glass Mapper. 9. Do the refactoring and fix build errors. 10. Publish and test the new solution. *** Notes *** - Disabled buttons are not available yet. - Make sure to disable nuget sources that are not needed. - Have a good network connection. - if you have too many projects in the solution, Run the tasks in smaller batches. - you can add your custom nuget packages to the config file (read more on GitHub)
